Good Morning Parents/Guardians, Students, and Staff,

Cranford Public Schools is pleased to offer our students, staff, and families daily messages of news and inspiration on our District Website. During World War II, President Roosevelt shared "Fireside Chats," a series of evening radio broadcasts to calm and encourage the nation. Similarly, Cranford staff members, in partnership with Cranford Radio, are providing a "Cranford Daily Message" featuring the daily weather, important historical events, and some short words of wisdom. These audio messages can be accessed on our by clicking the "Cranford Daily Message" (CDM) logo on the district website or by clicking here.
https://www.cranfordschools.org/site/Default.aspx?PageID=1365

Good afternoon,

Over the past three weeks, the District has provided devices and access to all who have expressed a need. As it appears that the community currently has the necessary technology resources, the technology department will now focus its efforts on providing technology support and will do so from off-site.

Should you need any technology support, please do not hesitate to contact the technology department by calling 908-709-8876 or emailing cps-tech@cranfordschools.org.

We are in this together and we will get through this together!

post_text:
Dear Parent/Guardian:

Central registration for students who will be new to Cranford (kindergarten, first grade, SNAPPY, READY, or any other grade level) for the 2020-2021 school year will be done online followed by an in-person appointment at Lincoln School (playground entrance) between the hours of 8:15 a.m. - 3:30 p.m. on Tuesday, February 18 through Friday, February 21. There will be limited appointments available on Saturday, February 22, 2020. If your child is currently enrolled in the district, (i.e. SNAPPY, READY, kindergarten) you DO NOT need to re-register.

Please carefully read the attached letter and follow the instructions. Please share this correspondence with neighbors who have school-age children.

Please go to https://www.cranfordschools.org/ to view the instructions.

post_text: Cranford Public Schools is proud of our Performing and Fine Arts program, led by Mr Anthony Rafaniello.
shared_text:
Rotary Club of Cranford, New Jersey
December 5, 2019 at 11:14 AM ·

What a great morning! Mr. Anthony Rafaniello, the head of Performing and Fine Arts for the entire Cranford School District presented to us about all the fantastic programs in the Arts available to Cranford Students. Mr. Raf has grown the programs to over 100 events this year. Get out and see a show, play, or performance and see our local talent. Fellow Cranford Rotarian, and Superintendent of Schools, Dr. Scott Rubin also joined with 4 senior students from The Cranford Madrigals chorale Group to make this meeting one of the years best! Thanks for all they do for our children and the celebration of the Arts!
#CranfordMadrigals #MrRafisawesome #CranfordSchoolDistrict
#PerformingandFineArtsRock
#ComeSeeWhatRotaryisabout

post_text:
The Cranford Public Schools Parent Academy proudly presents….

Like Us: An original film, created by middle school students, is a story about self-identified misfits who come together to achieve something greater, persevere, overcome their fears, and help one of their own. Learn about bullying awareness and prevention, and a message of acceptance and belonging. This film was screened at the Golden Door International Film Festival! Don’t miss it when it comes to Cranford!

Wednesday, October 23rd @ 6:30 pm
Evening family presentation for parents and students grades 2-8
Come for the snacks - stay for the movie (43 minutes) and interactive discussion after the movie!
HAS Auditorium

post_text:
All is well, but we wish to inform you of an incident that occurred today at Hillside Avenue School. Students reported to administration that another student had brought a knife to school. The administration immediately reached out to the Cranford Police Department who investigated the issue in partnership with the school.

A knife was discovered and appropriate measures have been taken. No threats were made and no student or staff member was in any danger.

The safety of our school community is a shared responsibility. We continue to encourage our entire community to please say something if you hear or see something.

post_text:
All is well at Cranford High School, but we wish to inform you of an incident. A Cranford High School student received a non-specific comment via SnapChat. It did not involve a threat regarding any of our schools. The school immediately reported the incident to the Cranford Police Department who are actively investigating and working with the legal team at SnapChat and other social media providers to identify the source of the comment.

Again, there is no credible threat to the Cranford School community. Out of an abundance of caution, there will be an increased police presence at Cranford High School tomorrow.

THE CRANFORD PUBLIC SCHOOLS PARENT ACADEMY IN PARTNERSHIP WITH
THE CRANFORD PTC AND LOCAL COMMUNITY ORGANIZATIONS
ARE SPONSORING A SERIES OF PRESENTATIONS TO SUPPORT THE
HEALTH AND WELLNESS OF OUR CHILDREN

Angst Movie: Anxiety Is Treatable, It’s Ok To Say

post_text: "The mission of the Cranford Municipal Alliance is to create, support and celebrate a positive, loving culture and community that is focused on the health and well-being of our children and refuses to condone underage drinking. One of the 2019 goals for the Municipal Alliance is to increase community engagement through our website and social media platforms. Artist, professor of animation, and Cranford mom Genevieve Okupniak Leonard has created an engaging website with sections appealing to students and parents. The Municipal Alliance invites the community to visit us on the internet at www.ourbestcranford.org or on facebook @CranfordMunicipalAlliance to learn more about the organization, how you can volunteer, and for information on events like the Annual Cranford Community Cookout on Sunday May 19th."

post_text:
Cranford Public Schools

Tuition-based Full Day Kindergarten Openings

There are currently 2 openings in the tuition-based full day kindergarten at Walnut Avenue School for the 2018-2019 school year. Applicants should be aware there is a tuition charge of $680 per month.

Please complete the application below and send to:
The Office of the Superintendent of Schools
132 Thomas Street
Cranford, New Jersey 07016

Applications can also be emailed to: cammarata@cranfordschools.org or faxed to: 908-272-7735.

For additional information or if you have any questions, you may call the Office of the Superintendent at (908) 709-6202.

Parents/Guardians will be responsible for transportation. Children attending the full day program will be placed in their neighborhood school for first grade in 2019-2020

Please visit the Cranford Public School's website, Latest News, to print the application.

post_text: Cranford Public School’s Japanese Program is searching for a host family to share their home with our Japanese assistant teacher! Learn about a different culture while sharing yours! Our district was selected by the Japan Foundation to have a native Japanese teaching assistant working with us and our language program. To help him or her get acclimated to life in the US, the Japanese teachers are searching for a host family within our community. There are two basic aspects in hosting: 1. Sharing your lifestyle with a person from another country 2. Providing a helping hand Timeline of hosting: July 31 , 2017 – November 30, 2017 If you have any questions, or would like to volunteer as a host family, please contact Wingate-sensei (wingate@cranfordschools.org). For more information about J-LEAP (Japanese Language Education Assistant Program), please visit: http://www.laurasian.org/jleap
